title: For Sale/Trade:  LWRC Rifle 223/ 5.56 read the story below * Price drop
postcontent:
I ordered the rifle in early 2007 (paid in full at ordering time...$2400) when LWRC was at their old location in Maryland and had limited production capability. Waited almost 4 months for the rifle. I had originally ordered what was then known as an SRT rifle, but after several phone calls, Darren called me and said that he would install one of their prototype barrels on an upper that would make it essentially a DMR platform. He sent me an email that I still have that explains that the barrel was made by Lothar-Walther with a polygonal bore and no M4 cuts. The profile is essentially an HBAR profile. Matt at NWT has one of these and will swear by it that it is a tack driver.

I had LWRC install a RRA two-stage trigger and a Vortex FH. Rifle has had no more than 380 round put through it (Mostly 22LR). I decided to keep this rifle as near mint since LWRC was moving to their new location to begin production of the 3rd gen rifles and thought this would be an excellent collector item some time in the future. However, the lady said if I want to purchase a new rifle, one has to go. The upper and lower are a pretty tight fit but I'm prepared to sell them separate.

title: For Sale:  gun parkerizing service

postcontent:
I can sandblast and parkerize your gun parts. I use a very fine glass bead media so no stamping or machine marks are distorted in any way. my prices are very fair and lower than anyone else i've ever heard of. as long as its not a reciever, the parts can be shipped to me and i'll ship them back after the parkerizing is complete. I do hold a valid FFL03 so anything falling under the C&R category can be shipped to me. many examples of my work can be seen on the CMP forums, as I mostly do park work on M1 Garands and M1 Carbine parts. I can do any gun though, not limited to the old US military rifles, I just do a lot of them.

I also do powder coating on pretty much anything, but i try to avoid powder coating any gun parts. it can be done, its just a lot of time consuming effort. The gas cyliniders on M1 garands cannot be parkerized, so I do powder coat a lot of them.

I also do media blasting on poretty much anything. most shops charge a fortune to do small parts, I dont. I do this sort of thing as a hobby out of my garage, so im not trying to earn a living or keep a business running, so I am able to do this kind of work real cheap. I dont have set prices, i just go by the list of parts you want done and whatr you want done to them. I also do work in trade for gun parts and anything else interesting. email me with a list of what you need done and we'll work something out.
thanks.

postcontent:
I have a very cool gun up for trade. Won't see many of these floating around

40S&W, chrome-lined barrel, steel-construction, extremely reliable, DA/SO/Triple-action pistol.

The Triple-Action is pretty neat; essentially, it allows for the hammer to be manually dropped without the need for a decocker, and to snap into single-action with pressure on the trigger. Ideal for carry (what I've used it for over the past year).

For an example of the tri-action, check out this video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P89vfQUJVCQ

A beautiful, accurate (I'm more accurate with this than with my M&P or Kahr), and well-constructed gun. I've not had a single FTF out of this in ~500 rounds.

Some slight holster wear on the finish, but in great shape.
